gen": "f", "num": "p"}, {"role": "past_1mp", "form": "بِنّا", "in_corpus": true, "count": 97, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}, {"role": "past_1ms", "form": "بِنْتُ", "in_corpus": true, "count": 69, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "s"}, {"role": "present_1ms", "form": "أَبِين", "in_corpus": true, "count": 9, "asp": "i", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "s"}, {"role": "present_1mp", "form": "نَبِين", "in_corpus": true, "count": 2, "asp": "i", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}], "frequency_in_corpus": 43274, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 5, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 7}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n3365", "n3584", "n3666", "n3658"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8E"}}, "translations": {"en": "to separate", "fa": "جدا شدن", "ur": "الگ ہونا", "tr": "ayırmak", "id": "memisahkan", "bn": "বিচ্ছিন্ন হওয়া", "es": "separarse", "fr": "séparer", "de": "sich trennen", "ru": "разделять", "zh": "分离"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to separate, to become distinct, to sunder"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be or become evident, to come out, to be or become clearly visible by way of separation"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to part, to become separated (from)", "tags": ["intransitive"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "builder"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ben tree, horseradish tree (the Moringa oleifera of Arabia and India, which produces oil of ben)", "tags": ["collective"], "examples": [{"text": "بان شجرة معروفة لها ثمرة حبّها أكبر من الحمص مائل إلى البياض طيب الرائحة وله لبّ دهني قال الشيخ الرئيس إنه ينفع من البرص والكلف والبهق وآثار القروح وينفع من الثآليل أيضا في المراهم وطبخه ينفع من وجع الأسنان مضمضة وقال غيره ينفع من الجرب ويقطع الرعاف.", "english": "The ben is a well-known tree with a fruit the grains of which are larger than chickpeas with a tendency towards white and a nice smell and an oily pulp about which Šayḵ ar-Raʾīs says that it helps against leprosy and melasmata and vitiligo and traces of ulcers and it helps against warts, too, and the salves and decocts applied by bandage are useful against toothache, and another author said it relives scabies and staunches nosebleed."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "Egyptian willow (Salix aegyptiaca L.)", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ban, a title in the Southeastern Europe"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the active participle of بَنَى (banā, “to build, to erect, to construct”).\n\nFrom ب و ن (b w n), as also بَنَان (banān, “finger”), a reference to the fruit or branch shape, known for their elegance in Arabic poetry.\n\nFrom Ottoman Turkish بان (ban), from Proto-Slavic *banъ."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n3365", "headword_ar": "بَانٍ", "root": "bnY", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Building, framing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "constructing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: accord. to A'Obeyd, its pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abonaA='N", "text_ar": "اَبْنَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajonaA='N", "text_ar": "اَجْنَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAnK", "text_ar": "جَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and hence the prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abonaAw^uhaA A^ajonaAw^uhaA", "text_ar": "اَبْنَاوُهَا اَجْنَاوُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajonaAw^uhaA A^abonaAw^uhaA", "text_ar": "اَجْنَاوُهَا اَبْنَاوُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The injurers thereof,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning this house ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*ihi Ald~aAr", "text_ar": "هٰذِهِ الدَّار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "),"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by demolishing it, are the builders thereof."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jnY", "text_ar": "جنى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ISd says, I am of opinion that these two pls. are not used except in this prov.: and J says, in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jnY", "text_ar": "جنى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", I think that the prov. is originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "junaAtuhaA bunaAtuhaA", "text_ar": "جُنَاتُهَا بُنَاتُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but IB affirms that it is not so: and he says that the prov. is applied to him who does, or makes, a thing without consideration, and commits a fault therein, which he repairs by undoing what he has done or made: it originated from the fact that the daughter of a certain king of El-Yemen, during his absence on a military expedition, built, by the advice of others, a house, which he, disliking it, commanded them to demolish. (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jnY", "text_ar": "جنى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 294.]) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A bridegroom:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaY EalaY", "text_ar": "بَنَى عَلَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aholihi", "text_ar": "اَهْلِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]. (TA.) And hence,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Any one going in to his wife."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qawosN baAniypN", "text_ar": "قَوْسٌ بَانِيةٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A bow cleaving to its string"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so that it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(the latter)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "almost breaks;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M;) the doing of which is a fault; (M;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAy^inapN", "text_ar": "بَايِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]: (S and M in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "byn", "text_ar": "بين"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnaApN", "text_ar": "بَانَاةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M, K) in the dial. of Teiyi: (T, M:) or the latter signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "widely separate from its string"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAy^inapN", "text_ar": "بَايِنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["M", "T", "S", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n3584", "headword_ar": "بَانٌ", "root": "bwn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "[a coll. gen. n., The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ben-tree;"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a species of moringa;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the present day;]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a kind of tree,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well known:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) n. un. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, Mgh, Msb:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its seed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grain,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hab~u AlbaAni", "text_ar": "حَبُّ البَانِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jawozu AlbaAni", "text_ar": "جَوْزُ البَانِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fusotuqu AlbaAni", "text_ar": "فُسْتُقُ البَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the glans unguentaria,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "nux unguentaria,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ben-nut,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has a good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pleasant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fragrant"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "oil,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duhonu AlbaAni", "text_ar": "دُهْنُ البَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "oil of ben"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S, Mgh, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and simply"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnN", "text_ar": "بَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the prefixed noun being suppressed: (Mgh:) [Az says,] it is the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnapN", "text_ar": "بَانَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". which is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain tree having a fruit,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "produce, which is perfumed with aromatics, after which its oil is expressed, of a good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fragrant"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "quality:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bnY", "text_ar": "بنى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its seed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grain, is good for"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "removing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affections of the skin termed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bara$", "text_ar": "بَرَش"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nama$", "text_ar": "نَمَش"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalaf", "text_ar": "كَلَف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaSaf", "text_ar": "حَصَف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bahaq", "text_ar": "بَهَق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saEafap", "text_ar": "سَعَفَة"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and the mange,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "scab, and for the peeling of the skin, applied in the form of a liniment with vinegar; and for hardness of the liver and the spleen, made into a beverage with vinegar; and a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mivoqaAl", "text_ar": "مِثْقَال"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thereof, drunk, is an emetic, which loosens crude phlegm:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) AHn says, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is a kind of tree that grows tall, in a straight,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an erect, manner, like as grows the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species of tamarisk called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^avol", "text_ar": "اَثْل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and its leaves are"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the kind termed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hadab", "text_ar": "هَدَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like those of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Avl", "text_ar": "اثل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "but its wood has no hardness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the n. un. is with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "P", "text_ar": "پ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": Aboo-Ziyád says,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is of the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "trees called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EiDaAh", "text_ar": "عِضَاه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and has long"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hdb", "text_ar": "هدب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "intensely green; it grows upon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hills,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what are termed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "haDob", "text_ar": "هَضْب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and its fruit resembles the pods of the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species of kidney-bean called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "luwbiyaA='", "text_ar": "لُوبِيَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "except that its greenness is intense; and in it is a seed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grain, from which is extracted the oil of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bAn", "text_ar": "بان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on account of the straightness of its growth and of the growth of its braches, and their length and tenderness, the poets liken thereto the tender girl of tall and beautiful,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "just, stature; saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaA^an~ahaA baAnapN", "text_ar": "كَاَنَّهَا بَانَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As though she were a ben-tree"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaA^an~ahaA guSonu baAnK", "text_ar": "كَاَنَّهَا غُصْنُ بَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As though she were a branch of the ben-tree"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], &c.: thus does Keys Ibn-El-Kha- teem: (M in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "byn", "text_ar": "بين"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) and so does Imra-el- Keys. (TA.) [See an ex. voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "barahorahapN", "text_ar": "بَرَهْرَهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b2- [It is also applied in the present day to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A species of willow,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "salix Aegyptia"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of Linnæus, properly called in Arabic"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xilaAf", "text_ar": "خِلَاف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and this is said to be meant by modern Arab poets when they liken an elegant girl to a twig of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bAn", "text_ar": "بان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but probably from their erroneously supposing this tree to be meant in the same case by the older poets.]"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Mgh", "Msb", "K", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n3666", "headword_ar": "بَانٌ", "root": "byn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "a coll. gen. n.: n. un. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bwn", "text_ar": "بون"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n3658", "headword_ar": "بَانَ", "root": "byn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, Mgh, Msb, K,) [aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabiynu", "text_ar": "يَبِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonuwnapN", "text_ar": "بَيْنُونَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buyuwnN", "text_ar": "بُيُونٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Mgh, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonN", "text_ar": "بَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became separated, severed, disunited,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cut off,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eani Al$~aYo'i", "text_ar": "عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnato", "text_ar": "بَانَتْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnato", "text_ar": "بَانَتْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biAlT~alaAqi", "text_ar": "بِالطَّلَاقِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a wife)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became separated by divorce,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eani Alr~ajuli", "text_ar": "عَنِ الرَّجُلِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the man."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnatN", "text_ar": "بَانَتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said of a girl, ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She became separated from her parents by marriage;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "she married:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISh, T:) as though she became at a distance from the house of her father. (ISh, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna", "text_ar": "بَانَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna bimaAlK", "text_ar": "بَانَ بِمَالٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabiynu", "text_ar": "يَبِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buyuwnN", "text_ar": "بُيُونٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonN", "text_ar": "بَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He became separated from his father,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mother,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "both, by property"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which he received from him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "her,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "them,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (AZ, T, M,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to be his alone:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ, T:) and ElFárisee states, on the authority of AZ, that one]"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 286}, {"kind": "text", "text": "says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna Eanohu", "text_ar": "بَانَ عَنْهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnahu", "text_ar": "بَانَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[the former app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he became separated thus from him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e., from his father; and the latter being syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abaAnahu", "text_ar": "اَبَانَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.]. (M.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna AlxaliyTu", "text_ar": "بَانَ الخَلِيطُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonN", "text_ar": "بَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonuwnapN", "text_ar": "بَيْنُونَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The partner,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "copartner,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sharer,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became separated from the person,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "persons, with whom he had been associated."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (T.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnato yadu Aln~aAqapi Eano janobihaA", "text_ar": "بَانَتْ يَدُ النَّاقَةِ عَنْ جَنْبِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buyuwnN", "text_ar": "بُيُونٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The fore leg of the she-camel became withdrawn,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "apart, from her side."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (T.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna", "text_ar": "بَانَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, Msb,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnuwA", "text_ar": "بَانُوا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabiynu", "text_ar": "يَبِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonN", "text_ar": "بَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonuwnapN", "text_ar": "بَيْنُونَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He separated himself,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it separated itself;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S; [in one copy of which it is said of a thing;]) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "they separated themselves:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a tribe, M, Msb)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "went, journeyed, went away,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "departed;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "went, removed, retired,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "withdrew itself, to a distance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "far away,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "far off."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna", "text_ar": "بَانَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, S, M, &c.,) aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabiynu", "text_ar": "يَبِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, Msb,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayaAnN", "text_ar": "بَيَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (T, S, Mgh, K;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AbAn", "text_ar": "ابان", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, S, M, &c.,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibaAnapN", "text_ar": "اـِبَانَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (T, Msb;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "by~n", "text_ar": "بيّن", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, S, M, &c.,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taboyiynN", "text_ar": "تَبْيِينٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tby~n", "text_ar": "تبيّن", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstbAn", "text_ar": "استبان", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (T, S, M, &c.,) all signify the same; (T, M, Msb;) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a thing, T, S, M, Mgh, or an affair, or a case, Msb)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "distinct, as though separate from others;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and thus,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "apparent, manifest, evident, clear, plain,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "perspicuous:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, Msb, K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became, known."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna AlHaq~u", "text_ar": "بَانَ الحَقُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The truth became apparent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "known"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AbAn", "text_ar": "ابان", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T.) And"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "AlS~uboHu li*iY Eayonayoni ↓ \n      qado bay~ana"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The dawn has become apparent to him who has two eyes:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a prov.: (S, M:) applied to a thing that becomes altogether apparent, or manifest. (Har p. 542.) And it is said in the Kur [ii. 257],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~u$odu mina AlgaY~i", "text_ar": "الرُّشْدُ مِنَ الغَىِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qado tabay~ana", "text_ar": "قَدْ تَبَيَّنَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The right belief hath become distinguished from error"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) And the lawyers, correctly, use the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaSawotK laA", "text_ar": "كَصَوْتٍ لَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "minohu HuruwfN", "text_ar": "مِنْهُ حُرُوفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yasotabiynu", "text_ar": "يَسْتَبِينُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Like a sound whereof letters are not distinguishable"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  [It seems to be indicated in the TA that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAna", "text_ar": "بَانَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabiynu", "text_ar": "يَبِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonN", "text_ar": "بَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonuwnapN", "text_ar": "بَيْنُونَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became, united,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "connected;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thus having two contr. meanings; but I have not found the verb used in this sense, though"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonN", "text_ar": "بَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies both disunion and union.]       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnahu", "text_ar": "بَانَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabiynu", "text_ar": "يَبِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonN", "text_ar": "بَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAnahu", "text_ar": "بَانَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yabuwnu", "text_ar": "يَبُونُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bawonN", "text_ar": "بَوْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bwn", "text_ar": "بون"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".       -A3-  See also 2, in two places."}], "source_refs": ["M", "Mgh", "Msb", "K", "ISh", "T", "AZ", "S"]}]}, "classical_definitions": {"source": "hawramani", "url": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86/", "headword_ar": "بان", "entries": [{"lexicon_id": "dictionary_48", "lexicon_en": "Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)", "lexicon_ar": "موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب", "permalink": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=130156#3f36d5", "body_html": "بان<br>من (ب و ن) نوع من الشجر طويل له ورق ليِّن يشبه به الحسان من النساء في الطول واللين. يستخدم للإناث."}]}, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}